      • fastReadMultipleBlock

        public byte[] fastReadMultipleBlock(byte[] blockAddress,
                                    byte numberOfBlocks)
                             throws STException
        Reads back a multiple blocks of data from a tag. The number of blocks read is numberOfBlocks + 1. The data rate of the response is twice as fast as a readMultipleBlock command.
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Address of the first block to read
        numberOfBlocks - Set to target blocks to read minus 1. The tag will actually return numberOfBlocks + 1 blocks.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        STException

      • fastReadMultipleBlock

        public byte[] fastReadMultipleBlock(byte[] blockAddress,
                                    byte numberOfBlocks,
                                    byte flag)
                             throws STException
        Reads back a multiple blocks of data from a tag. The number of blocks read is numberOfBlocks + 1. The data rate of the response is twice as fast as a readMultipleBlock command.
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Address of the first block to read
        numberOfBlocks - Set to target blocks to read minus 1. The tag will actually return numberOfBlocks + 1 blocks.
        flag - When the Option bit is set, the response includes the Block Security Status

        Throws:
